english:
  title: Inscribed on a Painting of the Eight Scenic Views
  author: An Ji
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Long did I not know the wondrous landscapes of Gyeongju.
    Now on a single bolt of silk they shimmer before me.
    Where deep ravines gather, the temple bell rings clear
    Beneath the luminous moon of evening.
    Where rain has cleared, the mountain mist blooms in color
    Along the forest's edge at dawning.
    The sun slants toward the river's mouth—the sail flies swift,
    Snow blankets the sandy shore—the geese descend in leisure.
    Without stepping beyond my courtyard gate, I have seen it all,
    And subtle rapture stirs within me, flowing into verses new.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Gyeongju (건주): An ancient Korean kingdom and cultural center, whose scenic beauty inspired classical landscape art.'
  - key: ''
    value: 'The Eight Scenic Views: A traditional genre of East Asian painting depicting famous landscapes, often capturing different seasons and times of day.'
  - key: ''
    value: The painting captures multiple scenes—moonlit ravines, clearing rain, sunset over water, and snow-covered shores—unified within a single silk scroll, allowing the viewer to journey through diverse landscapes without leaving home.
